-para (soylemedin ama iyidir herhalde)
-askerlik (cok uzun vadeli plan ama dayanmak kolay degil)
-paris'e gecme imkani (sor sorustur gecis oluyor mu)
-yurtdisindan tr'ye donus kolay sanki hep; gitmek zor benim anladigim
-turkiyede belli bi kontratin var; orda kalirsan ozgursun gitmekte, degil mi?

-teknik ise saplanip kalabirsin 
-sehrin kucuk olsu sorun,  tahmin edebiliyorum; ipswichte'de 5 gunde anladim ne demek istedigini.

The day after the May 17, 2015, finale of the drama Mad Men, which drew 3.3 million live and same-day viewers, the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 0.15%.

[9.03.2016 11:48:36] Burak Onal: Gulden Hanim merhaba,

Bu biraz short-notice oldu :) 

11 Mart Cuma gunu 10:30-12:00 icin herhangi bir engelim (toplanti ya da sehir disinda cikmak gibi) yok; ancak mulakata daha efektif hazirlanabilmek adina daha once bahsettiginiz 17 Mart tarihi veya sonrasi tercihimdir. Cunku takdir ederseniz ki 11 Mart Cuma gunu icin ciddi bir hazirlik yapmama zaman kalmadi. Mulakati yapacak danisman ekibinin yogunlugunu ve programlarina bu mulakati eklemenin zorlugunu tahmin edebiliyorum; ancak yukarida bahsettigim durumu goz onune alarak tarihi daha ileriye almaniz mumkun mudur? Bu hicbir sekilde mumkun degilse, 11 Mart icin verdiginiz gun ve saati konfirme etmek durumundayim. 

Cok tesekkurler vaktiniz icin.
Burak Onal
tr.linkedin.com/in/burakonal

Selamlar.

[17.07.2016 23:47:06] Burak Onal: The US Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) via a national security Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) has prohibited US airline carriers from flying to and from airports in Istanbul (IST and SAW) and Ankara (ESB). The restriction also bars all airline carriers and civil aviation operators, regardless of country of registry, from flying into the US from Turkey, either directly or via a third country. The NOTAM is in effect between 15 July and 31 August, and will be re-evaluated by FAA on 15 August.

Passengers planning to fly to the US from Turkey (or vice versa) between 15 July and 31 August will have to change carriers in a layover in order to accomplish such travel. However, the NOTAM by FAA does not advise against overflight of Turkish airspace, and flight operations transiting the country are unlikely to be directly affected."

Now both numbers are about half that.

They are among the last of the continentâ€™s makers of mobile devices and network equipment, which once ruled the world but are now lagging behind American and Chinese firms. If Ericsson and Nokia continue to shrink, only one European firm, Schneider Electric, would be left among the worldâ€™s 35 biggest tech companies by revenue.
